            "subject": "LU-4306 test: bump grace time in test_4a of s-q"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Bruno Faccini",
          "email": "bruno.faccini@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-02-10 10:07:11.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-03-03 17:20:36.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-5393 osd-ldiskfs: read i_size once to protect against race",
        "message": "LU-5393 osd-ldiskfs: read i_size once to protect against race\n\nThere have been several occurences of ASSERTION(local_nb[i].rc == 0)\nfailures in ost_brw_read(), where inode's i_size has changed due to\na racing write/growth beyond EOF. osd_read_prep() must protect\nhimself against this legal behavior by only reading i_size once.\n\nAlso removed m local variable declaration/usage apparently outdated.\n\nSigned-off-by: Bruno Faccini <bruno.faccini@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I5d931d5254b970e7031363f37114d0bad8b573fa\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/13707\nReviewed-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
